		"description": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-eece5741-7fff-fdd0-9bd6-4d76e0819447\" dir=\"ltr\">This divination pendulum consists of a pyramidal piece of polished celestite that dangles from a delicate gold chain. Its user may write the words &ldquo;yes&rdquo; and &ldquo;no&rdquo; on a piece of parchment, ask a question, and then dangle the pendulum above it. If the Narrator determines that the answer is clear, the pendulum will swing to either side, indicating the answer. If the answer is unclear or otherwise unable to be answered by a simple &ldquo;yes&rdquo; or &ldquo;no,&rdquo; it remains stationary. Once this ability has been used, it cannot be used again until the next dawn.</p>",
